sql:
SELECT total_points
FROM user_points
WHERE user_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- 'Admins' are users with the role 'admin';
- 'Editing permissions' refer to the control type 'edit' with the control value 'true';
- The calculation of points per session is total points divided by the number of sessions plus one to avoid division by zero.

- "stars that shine brighter than the average" refers to users who have earned more points than the average total points;
- "dipped into the treasure chest of points" refers to the number of times users have exchanged points;
- "luminous point total" refers to the total points earned by the users.

- 'guardians' refers to users with the role 'admin';
- 'lost more points than they've gained' refers to having a negative total point change;
- 'birth year marked by the turning of the century' refers to being born in the year 1990.

sql:
SELECT total_points
   FROM user_points
   WHERE total_points > 100;

SELECT user_id, total_points
FROM user_points
ORDER BY total_points DESC;

SELECT user_id, total_points
FROM user_points
ORDER BY total_points DESC;

SELECT user_id
FROM user_points
ORDER BY total_points DESC;

external_knowledge:
- 'shining stars' refers to users;
- 'accumulated a bountiful harvest' refers to earning more than 100 points;
- 'reward points' are points of the type 'rewards'.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(history_id) 
FROM control_history 
WHERE control_change = 'edit';

external_knowledge:
- "Bestowed with the keys to the castle" refers to users who have edit access (control type ID = 1);
- "The privilege to gaze upon its treasures" refers to users who have view access (control type ID = 2);
- "Accumulated points" are the total points earned by the user;
- "The number of times their points have been altered" refers to the total number of point changes recorded for each user.

- "top users" refers to users with the highest total points;
- "points" are the total points earned by the user;
- "roles" are the roles assigned to users, such as 'admin' or 'user'.

sql:
SELECT user_id, SUM(point_value) AS total_points
FROM points
GROUP BY user_id;

SELECT p.user_id, COALESCE(SUM(p.point_value), 0) AS total_points
FROM points p
GROUP BY p.user_id;

external_knowledge:
- 'stars' refers to users who have earned bonus points;
- 'gathered a treasure of bonus points' means users with a total bonus point value greater than 0;
- 'how much do they shine' refers to the total bonus points earned by each user;
- 'constellation of rewards' is a metaphorical way to describe the ranking of users by their total bonus points.

- "annual harvests" refers to the total points exchanged each year;
- "the past two years" corresponds to the date range '2022-01-01' to '2023-12-31';
- "the garden yielded more than 100 points" means the sum of points exchanged in a year is greater than 100.
